{"Body": "<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"> </span></p>\n<p>The following is the statement released by Trinity Students' Union, addressed to the Provost, Dr. John Hegarty. It was displayed on a large poster board in the windows of the Berkeley library and now sits facing the entrance.</p>\n<p><em>Dear Provost,</em></p>\n<p><em>The situation is very simple - students need books to learn. You boasted in the Irish Times this week about balancing Trinity's books. We think you've forgotten about the books that really count.</em></p>\n<p><em>These are our demands:</em></p>\n<p><em>1. Reverse the &euro;650,000 book-buying cut.</em></p>\n<p><em>2. Increase Library opening hours to the national average instead of cutting them further.</em></p>\n<p><em>3. Come to the library today, sit down with student representatives and hear student concerns.</em></p>\n<p>So far, the office of the Provost has not been in contact with the protesting students.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>", "Imageurl": "<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"> </span></p>\n<p>The following is the statement released by Trinity Students' Union, addressed to the Provost, Dr. John Hegarty. It was displayed on a large poster board in the windows of the Berkeley library and now sits facing the entrance.</p>\n<p><em>Dear Provost,</em></p>\n<p><em>The situation is very simple - students need books to learn. You boasted in the Irish Times this week about balancing Trinity's books. We think you've forgotten about the books that really count.</em></p>\n<p><em>These are our demands:</em></p>\n<p><em>1. Reverse the &euro;650,000 book-buying cut.</em></p>\n<p><em>2. Increase Library opening hours to the national average instead of cutting them further.</em></p>\n<p><em>3. Come to the library today, sit down with student representatives and hear student concerns.</em></p>\n<p>So far, the office of the Provost has not been in contact with the pro